BusinessName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: Indiana Primary Health Care Assoc Inc

IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: To advocate for access to quality primary health care for all those uninsured and under insured residing in Indiana and to support the growth and development of community-oriented primary care initiatives.
IRS990.MissionDesc: To advocate for access to quality primary health care for all those uninsured and under insured residing in Indiana and to support the growth and development of community-oriented primary care initiatives.
IRS990.Desc: Provide technical assistance, including training to community health centers as well as National Health Service Cooperative site development and recruitment/retention of health care professionals.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: Provide development, monitoring, technical assistance and evaluation services to sites funded through the tobacco settlement monies. Also to provide information regarding shortage designation areas of medically under served population.

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: Navigator - As established by the Affordable Care Act, to assist and educate consumers regarding the Federally-facilitated Marketplace and State Partnership Marketplaces. Train staff and maintain expertise in eligibility, enrollment, and program specifications and conduct public education activities to raise awareness about the Marketplace. Provide information and services to consumers in a fair, accurate, and impartial manner, which includes providing information that assist consumers with submitting the eligibility application; clarifying the distinctions among health coverage options and the health coverage selection process.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Indiana Primary Health Care Association, Inc. (IPHCA) has been granted an exemption from income taxes as a not-for-profit organization under Section 501(c)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code; therefore, no expense or liability for income taxes has been recognized in the accompanying financial statements. Management believes that IPHCA has adequately addressed all relevant tax positions and that there are no unrecorded tax liabilities. IPHCA believes it is no longer subject to income tax examination for years prior to 2012.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part III, Line 4d: Other Program Services Description
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: OTHER PROGRAM SERVICES 4: The primary goal of the STAR (Strengthen * Transform * Adapt * Replicate) Community Health Centers Initiative (The STAR Initiative) is to build innovative, scalable, and sustainable CHCs in order to succeed in a rapidly changing environment. The STAR Initiative is a three-year quality improvement program focused on strengthening the financial operations of community health centers. The quality improvement areas include: cross functional team decision making, revenue cycle optimization, increasing operational efficiencies, and improving access to capital. The program is funded by The Kresge Foundation. OTHER PROGRAM SERVICES 5: Navigator - As established by the Affordable Care Act, to assist and educate consumers regarding the Federally-facilitated Marketplace and State Partnership Marketplaces. Train staff and maintain expertise in eligibility, enrollment, and program specifications and conduct public education activities to raise awareness about the Marketplace. Provide information and services to consumers in a fair, accurate, and impartial manner, which includes providing information that assist consumers with submitting the eligibility application; clarifying the distinctions among health coverage options and the health coverage selection process.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 11b: Form 990 Review Process
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Indiana Primary Health Care Association, Inc.'s Form 990 and all related schedules, statements and attachments are reviewed by the Chairman of the Finance Committee and then presented and approved by the Finance Committee and the Board of Directors prior to filing these tax returns with the Internal Revenue Service.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 12c: Explanation of Monitoring and Enforcement of Conflicts
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Indiana Primary Health Care Association, Inc.'s conflict of interest statement is reviewed annually and each Board member must complete a form declaring any conflicts. On every vote the Chairperson of the Board of Directors gives members an opportunity to register their vote as an abstention due to conflict of interest.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 15a: Compensation Review & Approval Process - CEO, Top Management
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Indiana Primary Health Care Association, Inc.'s Board of Directors' Personnel Committee addresses the general wage structure which would cover all employees. They review comparative wage data from local sources and from other Primary Care Associations from around the nation in determining the wage structure. The actual compensation level for the CEO is determined by the Executive Committee of the Board without staff involvement.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 15b: Compensation Review and Approval Process for Officers and Key Employees
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Indiana Primary Health Care Association, Inc.'s Board of Director's Personnel Committee addresses the general wage structure which covers all other employees. They review comparative wage data from local sources and from other Primary Care Associations from around the nation in determining the wage structure.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part VI, Line 19: Other Organization Documents Publicly Available
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Indiana Primary Health Care Association, Inc. makes its governing documents, conflict of interest policy and financial statements, as applicable, available to the public upon written request made to the attention of our Chief Executive Officer and received at our corporate office address.
